 many tests set jgroups.use.jdk_logger. It’s a bit odd that the build sets a custom logger, but it seems it's used at native runtime.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying configuration setup**\\n\\nI need to make sure the \\\"reason\\\" field is concise. For the deterministic setup, I have some concrete reasons. For Slf4j, the JGroups POM declares slf4j-api as optional, and LogFactory detects the Logger only by Class.forName. The WildFly documentation mentions a dependency for OpenSSL, which my current tests are using to check SSL provider detection. However, I wonder if \\\"needs setup beyond normal generated scaffold\\\" includes optional paths. I would phrase it as \\\"advisory_preparation\\\" instead of \\\"must to compile,\\\" since the action values would be no_action or advisory_preparation.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"JGroups core coverage can be local-only, but meaningful existing coverage relies on loopback network properties and optional dynamically loaded logging/SSL integrations.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.slf4j:slf4j-api:1.7.31\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"JGroups declares SLF4J as an optional dependency and LogFactory detects org.slf4j.Logger via Class.forName; adding it lets tests exercise the optional logging path used by normal deployments.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.wildfly.openssl:wildfly-openssl:2.1.1.Final\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"JGroups SslContextFactory probes org.wildfly.openssl.OpenSSLProvider and org.wildfly.openssl.SSL reflectively; adding the optional provider enables SSL provider detection coverage.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Set JGroups tests to local networking: use system properties jgroups.bind_addr=127.0.0.1 and java.net.preferIPv4Stack=true for JVM and native test runs. Prefer SHARED_LOOPBACK/SHARED_LOOPBACK_PING stacks over UDP/TCP multicast for channel tests. Set logging properties before LogFactory is first loaded; use jgroups.use.jdk_logger=true for most tests, or define a test custom Log implementation and set jgroups.log_class when deliberately exercising custom logger loading. Avoid external services: JDBC_PING can be covered with an in-test fake java.sql.Driver rather than a database container.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Default UDP/TCP or multicast stacks may be flaky or hang in CI/native-image runs; keep generated tests loopback-only unless explicitly testing transport setup.\",\n    \"LogFactory and SslContextFactory do static classpath/property detection, so tests must set properties before those classes are initialized.\",\n    \"WildFly OpenSSL is optional and may fall back to the JDK SSL provider depending on native availability; tests should accept either provider state unless specifically validating OpenSSL.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_062a32876ca6efbd016a428206df248190bce92066d097dc52\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1486, "output": 1405, "cacheRead": 44544, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 47435, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782743542478, "responseId": "resp_062a32876ca6efbd016a4281f6fb408190bbb2a9e62dd42d63"}, "toolResults": []}
